ication policies web checkin  the inside scoop   should you checkin online or at the airport other advantages include in addition to being able to hold on to your seat online checkin gives you more flexibility in seat assignments the week prior to departure is often full of seat changes as travelers move around the plane getting upgraded and finding the best seats at the twenty four hour window better seats can also open up  printing your boarding pass ahead of time of course saves time but if you don’t have a printer you can show an airline agent at the airport your id and they’ll print it out for you some airlines offer the option of downloading your boarding pass to a mobile device or a selfservice kiosk to print it out  some airlines offer bonus frequent flyer miles for web checkin web checkin is a service that allows you to check in for your flight from anywhere there’s an internet connection in most cases you can select your seats and check in from  hours up until  hours before your flight and if your itinerary includes a connection to a carrier that the airline has an eticketing and online checkin agreement with you may check in for your flights with those carriers as well the majority of sizeable domestic airlines offer web checkin including delta united us airways american northwest continental alaska  jet blue and southwest some major international airlines also feature web checkin including air canada british airways and virgin atlantic however not all international airlines have adopted the system while checking in online is a great time saver like so many online exchanges there are drawbacks it’s a good idea to be aware of both the pros and the cons before you take the web checkin plunge have a tip to shareemail us at helloegenciacom what’s so great about it one of the best things about web checkin is that you can arrive at the airport much closer to takeoff you just need to be at the gate by the time the door is closed  to  minutes before departure typically those who are last to check in at the airport are the first to get bumped if the flight is overbooked however with online checkin you can lose your keys forget your wallet drive back home to retrieve it get stuck in traffic arrive at the airport just in the nick of time and your seat still won’t be given away even if you dont make it at all  your seat will be held until the last possible moment only if you havent showed up at that point and the spare seats are needed will the airline give away your seat  okay so what’s not so great while some people have concerns about how or when theyre going to check their luggage in and are worried about its integration into the system when they checkin online that really is a nonissue the biggest restriction is that once you check in you cannot make any changes to your reservation so if your plans could change online checkin is not a good fit for your travel plans once you checkin an airline imposed change fee will be applied youll also need to call an egencia travel agent to contact the airline for you and cancel the check in  additionally you may not be eligible to use online flight checkin if you are traveling on a military fare traveling with a pet traveling with an oxygen container traveling with an infant under the age of two an unaccompanied minor about the author jennifer carrara is a writer for egencia her background includes positions as an advertising copywriter marketing writer and magazine editor currently she writes proposals answering every question in the book about the value of a travel management partner – from how to redeem an unused airline ticket to configuring a global travel program if you travel with only carryon luggage boarding is further streamlined but even if you need to check your bags most carriers have separate lines at ticketing for full versus luggage only checkin the luggage only line always moves faster because all you have to do is scan your boarding pass drop off your bags and head through security  things to keep in mind when you checkin web checkin is not available on all itineraries and it isnt always perfectly clear which those might be as they vary by airline and international law most airline web sites maintain a faq list clearly outlining policies and restrictions  when traveling multiple leg trips on a single itinerary you will be prompted to print individual boarding passes for each leg to checkin online or not that is the question if your itinerary is complex you might be better off checking in at the airport but if your travel plans are straightforward checking in online is a simple procedure that you would do well to adopt  not only will you save time but you will not contribute to the long lines and subsequent long wait that other travelers who need extra assistance must endure all in all web checkin is a great choice for the web savvy traveler pros of web checkinsaves time  you can arrive at the airport closer to takeoff less likely to get bumped  your seat will be held until the last possible momentmore flexibility with seat assignmentsbonus frequent flyer points with some airlinescons of web checkinyou can no longer change your flight  without a change fee  you essentially cash in your ticket when you checkin onlinenot all itineraries will be eligible for online checkin varies based on airlines policy and complexity of trip you will not be able to checkin online for your return trip at the same time you checkin for your outbound flight unless your return flight is within  hours of departure  it’s a good idea to have more than one contact phone number and a contact phone number for the destination you are at in case of a delay or cancellation for your return flight otherwise the airline has no way to contact you  rules on how long in advance of your flight you can check in vary considerably some airlines allow passengers to checkin online within  hours of departure time to as late as  minutes prior to scheduled departure time others require that checkin occur on the actual day of travel meaning after am on the day of travel and these airlines may stop accepting online checkins at  to  minutes before flight time since international travel generally requires that you arrive at your gate earlier than domestic travel checkin deadlines are often earlier online as well  egencia the egencia logo expedia expediacom and the airplane logo are either registered trademarks or trademarks of expedia inc in the us and other countries other trademarks mentioned herein may be the property of their respective owners  egencia llc all rights reserved cst see our privacy policy if you have questions about egencia communication policies egencia corporate travel management  egencia customer login overview of egencia for travel managers are you familiar with egencias booking tool if not spend  minutes and watch this video it covers two important sections within egencia  department codes and policy you will see for yourself how easy it is to manage travel with egencias online tool complete the form or call  to learn more about egencias corporate travel management program first name last name company name work email work phone country state your companys annual travel spend lead source original medium original source original campaign original content original term recent medium recent source recent campaign recent content recent term submit your secure transaction completed your transaction is complete click the submit button to continue web checkin  the inside scoop   should you checkin online or at the airport other advantages include in addition to being able to hold on to your seat online checkin gives you more flexibility in seat assignments the week prior to departure is often full of seat changes as travelers move around the plane getting upgraded and finding the best seats at the twenty four hour window better seats can also open up  printing your boarding pass ahead of time of course saves time but if you d